articles.description: Fletcher Magee had 21 points to lead five players in double figures and Wofford cruised to an 84-69 victory over Western Carolina on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Wofford rolls to 84-69 win over Western Carolina

articles.description: USC's Jordan McLaughlin finds Chimezie Metu inside to give the Trojans the winning bucket over the Ducks.
articles.headline: Trojans win on alley-oop

images.caption: USC's Jordan McLaughlin finds Chimezie Metu inside to give the Trojans the winning bucket over the Ducks.
images.name: Trojans win on alley-oop

articles.description: Corey Kispert led a balanced attack with 14 points and No. 9 Gonzaga beat Loyola Marymount 76-46 on Thursday night to retain at least a share of first place in the West Coast Conference.
articles.headline: Williams leads No. 9 Gonzaga over Loyola Marymount 76-46

articles.description: USC works the ball around to Elijah Stewart who nails the three to give the Trojans the lead over the Ducks.
articles.headline: USC's Stewart knocks down clutch 3-pointer

images.name: USC's Stewart knocks down clutch 3-pointer

articles.description: Josh Ajayi had 26 points to go with 14 rebounds to help South Alabama continue its domination of Appalachian State with a 77-66 win over the Mountaineers in Sun Belt Conference action on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Ajayi has 26 points, 14 boards as South Alabama wins 77-66

videos.description: Jared Harper chases down Ole Miss' Bruce Stevens and gets a huge block.
videos.headline: Auburn's little guy skies for huge block

videos.description: Breein Tyree sees the clock winding down then kicks it over to Bruce Stevens who drans the 3-pointer right before the half.
videos.headline: Ole Miss' Stevens hits clutch 3-pointer

videos.description: Horace Spencer blocks Rebels' Breein Tyree and then stares him down after play.
videos.headline: Tigers' Spencer patrols the rim

videos.description: Bryce Brown penetrates into the paint then makes a nice dish to Mustapha Heron for the layup to take the lead 53-52.
videos.headline: Tigers' Brown-Heron connection gives them lead

videos.description: Davion Mitchell drives baseline and threads the needle to Bryce Brown who swishes in the corner 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Tigers' Brown cashes in 3-pointer

videos.description: Desean Murray finds Mustapha Heron slashing to the basket and he has to tap the ball twice in mid-air for the and-1 bucket. The Tigers go up 61-54 against the Rebels after the free throw.
videos.headline: Tigers' Heron makes crazy shot to extend lead

videos.description: Coach Bruce Pearl had T-shirts made for the Tigers that say "4-14" on them, after critics predicted Auburn would finish with a losing record in the SEC.
videos.headline: Auburn sports bulletin board material from critics

videos.description: Desean Murray blocks the shot then tries saving the ball but crashes into referee causing him to spin and fall.
videos.headline: Tigers' Murray hustle play knocks over referee

videos.description: Jared Harper drives and then lobs it to Anfrenee McLemore who throws down the alley-oop on the defender.
videos.headline: Auburn putting on a show with splash play

videos.description: Bryce Brown pokes the ball away then throws down a vicious tomahawk dunk.
videos.headline: Tigers' Brown seals game with exclamation point
